Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with high-rate, non-orthogonal space-time block coded (STBC) large-multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which are related to information theory and signal processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed low-complexity detection and channel estimation scheme can be applied to wireless communication systems, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a training-based iterative detection/channel estimation scheme for large STBC MIMO systems, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The high data rate wireless applications enabled by large-MIMO systems can involve multimedia data transmission. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of wireless communication technologies.
